10/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The National Service for Organised Crime Fighting (NSOCF) and the US Drug Enforcement Administration have broken a synthetic drug trafficking ring, NSOCF's deputy chief Colonel Venelin Velikov announced Thursday (9 September).
He added that 220kg of amphetamines, worth about 22m euros, were seized in the joint operation in Sofia.
Four people -- two Syrians and two Bulgarians -- were arrested.
In other news, Bulgaria and the European Monitoring Centre for Drugs and Drug Addiction (EMCDDA) sealed an agreement Thursday, allowing Bulgaria to fully participate in EMCDDA's work.
Similar accords were signed with Romania and Turkey this year.
(Dnevnik - 10/09/04;
Mediapool, EU Web site - 09/09/04)
